@emafermon are you using any plugins? did you import anything from older NetBeans versions on first start?

If you want to help with this issue, could you replace a class in a jar so that we get a bit more information?
1) backup `netbeans_14/java/modules/org-netbeans-modules-form.jar`
2) replace `ClassSource.class` (the 3 files in the zip) in `org-netbeans-modules-form.jar:org/netbeans/modules/form/project/`
3) start NB repeat the test again, new project -> create JFrame form, post the new exception
4) now you can restore the old jar, or you keep it - you decide :)

[org.netbeans.modules.form.project.zip](https://github.com/apache/netbeans/files/9091324/org.netbeans.modules.form.project.zip)

I only added this defensive check to get a trace from the root of the problem:
```diff
diff --git a/java/form/src/org/netbeans/modules/form/project/ClassSource.java b/java/form/src/org/netbeans/modules/form/project/ClassSource.java
index 924a247718..37bf2b6738 100644
--- a/java/form/src/org/netbeans/modules/form/project/ClassSource.java
+++ b/java/form/src/org/netbeans/modules/form/project/ClassSource.java
@@ -50,6 +50,9 @@ public final class ClassSource {
         this(className, entries, null);
     }
     public ClassSource(String className, Collection<? extends Entry> entries, String typeParameters) {
+        if (entries.contains(null)) {
+            throw new IllegalArgumentException("entries contains null entry: "+entries);
+        }
         this.className = className;
         this.entries = entries;
         this.typeParameters = typeParameters;
```

@mbien if this is fixed with dev, is this also fixed by #4165 ?

> Is there a way of getting the dev version to launch using the v14 config and project data?

Use `Tools / Options / Import`.  If you're picking up some options / projects already, it suggests you've used a dev build before?  In which case, I would consider deleting the dev userdir and cachedir, doing a clean start, then importing.

> @mbien if this is fixed with dev, is this also fixed by #4165 ?

@neilcsmith-net probably not. #4165 won't make completion windows appear even if there are more items available (after a successful completion) unless it is specifically requested in the completion template token. Thats all. It changes nothing regarding threading. Completion is invoked the same way via SwingUtilites.invokeLater().

So the bug might be still there (assuming there is a bug) just hidden. E.g if you press ctrl+space fast enough you could replicate the old behavior and potentially trigger the same issue.
